text: San Leandro is a large suburban town in Alameda County, California, United States. The population was 91,008 at the 2020 census. It is on the eastern shore of San Francisco Bay, between Oakland to the northwest and Hayward to the southeast. == References == == Other websites == *Official website of the city of San Leandro *San Leandro Chamber of Commerce *San Leandro High School *San Leandro Bytes *San Leandro Times *San Leandro Online Category:1872 establishments in California Category:Cities in California Category:Cities in the San Francisco Bay Area Category:Settlements in Alameda County, California
